<DATELINE>SNELLVILLE, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three children who spent two years in a tent in the <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION> wilderness after allegedly being kidnapped by their father are back in <LOCATION> Georgia </LOCATION> with their mother. They were reunited Thursday with <PERSON> Amelia </PERSON> <PERSON> Doellefeld </PERSON> in a <LOCATION> Bangor </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION>, courthouse. By evening, they were home in this town about 20 miles northeast of <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>. `` I just remember my legs were shaking _ I was shaking all over,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Doellefeld </PERSON> said, referring to the tearful reunion. <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> agents arrested the father, 52-year-old <PERSON> Tex </PERSON> <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Doellefeld </PERSON>, as a fugitive from justice in the tiny central <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION> town of <LOCATION> Greenville </LOCATION> late Wednesday. He was released from the Penobscot County Jail after posting $ 20,000 bond, a jail spokesman said. <LOCATION> Gwinnett </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> authorities began extradition proceedings after Gwinnett District Attorney <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Lawler </PERSON> said he opposed Doellefeld's release The children _ <PERSON> Jason </PERSON>, 13; <PERSON> Beth </PERSON>, 11; and <PERSON> Max </PERSON>, 9 _ were dirty but in good condition. `` I was talking to <PERSON> Beth </PERSON> and she said it was like being on vacation,'' said <PERSON> Lyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Mealor </PERSON>, the children's aunt. `` I thought many times they were dead and just not knowing was the worst,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Doellefeld </PERSON> said. `` Are they hurt? Are they safe? Are their needs being met? At one point, it was so black. `` One night I said to myself, I've got to do something or else I am going to die,'' she said. Officials in <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION> said <PERSON> Doellefeld </PERSON> was discovered after school officials recognized photographs of the children printed on a