<PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Presley </PERSON>, that was already on the floor and with his permission voted 48-13 to amend it by adding the wiretap measure The amended bill is scheduled for a floor vote next Thursday. The bill would allow police with approval of the attorney general or a district attorney to petition a <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> for a wiretap authorization. The police would have to show that it was likely that a drug possession or sale offense had been or would be committed.
