<BYLINE>By MERRILL HARTSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> and his wife, <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON>, had an adjusted gross income of $ 345,359 in 1987 with a federal tax liability of $ 86,638, according to tax returns released today. That income was $ 8,990 above what the <ORGANIZATION> Reagans </ORGANIZATION> reported for 1986, while their tax bill rose $ 5,822. Taxes as a percentage of the <ORGANIZATION> Reagans </ORGANIZATION>' gross income rose from 25.1 percent to 27.5 percent. The couple had $ 67,392 withheld for federal income taxes last year and paid an additional $ 30,000 in quarterly payments, for a total of $ 97,392. That means they paid $ 10,754 above what they owed the government. Rather than getting a refund, the couple elected to apply that amount to their 1988 taxes. Included in the gross income was the president's $ 200,000 salary, $ 54,179 in interest income, $ 46,208 in capital gains and $ 29,711 in income from his pension for serving as governor of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> from 1967-75. The income also included $ 1,526 in appearance fees paid to the president and Mrs. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>. This included $ 1,312 paid to <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> for his appearance on <ORGANIZATION> NBC-TV </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Tonight'' show and $ 214 paid to Mrs. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> in residual talent fees for re-runs of two programs in which she had appeared in 1986. White House spokesman <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said the $ 1,312 fee paid to the president was `` required to be paid ... under union agreements'' in the television industry, and said that the $ 1,312 was donated along with other money to his alma matter, <ORGANIZATION> Eureka </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION> in Illionois. Charitable deductions totaled $ 25,407. After deductions, the <ORGANIZATION> Reagans </ORGANIZATION>' total taxable income was $ 263,767. The tax returns were released a day after White House chief of staff <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> <P