N> Reagans </ORGANIZATION>, based on fair-market value rental estimates from two independent appraisers. The home, on a 1 \ - acre property in the poshest section of <ORGANIZATION> Bel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, is near the <PERSON> Kirkeby </PERSON> estate where the television series `` Beverly Hillbillies'' It has a heated swimming pool and a three-car garage. Real estate sources estimate the monthly rent at $ 12,000 to $ 15,000, based on fair-market value. The Reagans are known to feel strongly about their privacy, and the first lady during the early years of the administration made it clear she wanted information about the president's health handled carefully by the White House press office. And the first couple has chafed over past reporting of difficulties involving <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> children and relatives. On Thursday, <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> was asked if the president and his wife were upset by the spate of media reports on the home-leasing deal. `` Oh, I do n't think so,'' said <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>, standing outside a seaside resort hotel cottage not far from <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s mountaintop ranch. `` I think after eight years, they've come to understand that that occurs, and while they understand it, they may not like it, but they are not angry about it. `` The White House, the president and the first lady went to great lengths to make sure that this was an arms-length transaction, that there was a full appraisal of the rental property and that all of the i's were dotted and the t's were crossed,'' he said. <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> said that <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> and his wife have handled the leasing of the home `` in precisely the right way and really beyond legitimate criticism.'' The property was purchased in August 1986 by the consortium, which has incorporated itself as <ORGANIZATION> Wall </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Realtor <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Hyland </PERSON> of the <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> firm of <PERSON> Alvarez </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Hyland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Young </PERSON>, said that with rising prices since the purchase, the land alone is worth $ 3 million `` They got a great buy,'' he said. `` They bought it for land value. As far as I am concerned, they got the house for free.'' Realtor <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Aaroe </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Jon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Douglas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said the house, built in 1954, still has the original kitchen and needs a great deal of renovation.
