<HEAD>Police Say Hostage Situation Was a Charade</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhotos HX1-2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YORK, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A man who was killed by police after pretending to hold a teen-age girl hostage for three hours had a history of erratic behavior and family problems, said a woman who had been one of his many foster mothers. <PERSON> Israel </PERSON> <PERSON> Ramos </PERSON>, 19, died Wednesday at <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> from a single gunshot wound to the stomach to end a three-hour standoff in which he held police at bay from his apartment with what turned out to be plastic water pistols. Police originally thought <PERSON> Ramos </PERSON> had taken a 15-year-old girl hostage, but after the shooting she told authorities the drama was a charade and she was a willing participant. <PERSON> Debbie </PERSON> <PERSON> Ocasio </PERSON>, who took in <PERSON> Ramos </PERSON> when he was 15 and had a history of family problems, said: `` I knew he was erratic, so I wanted to help him. I knew that if I could just talk with him, that would help.'' <PERSON> Ramos </PERSON> was born in <LOCATION> Puerto </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rico </LOCATION> and spent most of his life on the streets in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, said Mrs. <PERSON> Ocasio </PERSON>. He came to <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> with his mother about four years ago. <PERSON> Ramos </PERSON>' mother suffered from mental disorders and frequently spent long periods in state hospitals, forcing her son to live with foster families, Mrs. <PERSON> Ocasio </PERSON> said. His father remained in <LOCATION> Puerto </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rico </LOCATION>. While living with the Ocasios, <PERSON> Ramos </PERSON> attended high school, maintained a B average and saw a counselor, she said. But his life always took a turn for the worse whenever he saw his mother. `` Something about her just set him off,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Ocasio </PERSON> said. Hoping to stabilize him, Mrs. <PERSON> Ocasio </PERSON> said she arranged for <PERSON> Ramos </PERS