<TEXT>
 Elsewhere in television: WHITHER PAULEY? _ With <PERSON> Jane </PERSON> <PERSON> Pauley </PERSON> out for the week that ended April 1, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Today'' show dropped to a virtual tie with <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Good Morning America'' after a 19-week winning streak Both shows had a rating of 4.6, a percentage of total homes with televisions. `` Today'' had a 20 share to <ORGANIZATION> GMA </ORGANIZATION>'s 19 _ that's the percentage of the audience actually watching TV. <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> <PERSON> Shriver </PERSON> substituted for <PERSON> Pauley </PERSON> that week. <PERSON> Bryant </PERSON> <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> is off this week, and <PERSON> Phil </PERSON> <PERSON> Donahue </PERSON> is substituting. `` CBS This Morning'' struggles along in third place. Last week it had a 2.3 rating and a 10 share.
